    "body": "I think we are turning a little in circles here. Solidity when used in standard-json mode is fully platform independent. This is a requirement so that you can re-compile the same source to the same binary on all platforms. Standard-json does not care about the directory separator on the platform in is used on. It will always use slash. If you are running a web server on windows, the URLs you use are still of the form `http://github.com/ethereum/solidity` and not `http:\\\\github.com\\ethereum\\solidity`. Relative links inside html files also follow the same pattern as import statements in solidity.\r\n\r\nWhat do you use to create the standard-json input? This component should translate the back slashes to forward slashes.",
